==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[summetria]]'', originally from Greek

===Adjective===
'''symmetric'''

#Same as '''[[symmetrical]]'''.
#{{settheory}} Of a [[relation]] ''R'' on a [[set]] ''S'', such that ''xRy'' [[if and only if]] ''yRx'' for all [[member]]s ''x'' and ''y'' of ''S'' (that is, if the relation holds between any element and a second, it also holds between the second and the first).
#:''"Is a sibling of" is a '''symmetric''' relation.''

====Related terms====
*[[asymmetric]]
*[[symmetry]]

